  "westernTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "With its unique profile of fatty acids, tocopherols (Vitamin E), squalene, sterols and phenolic compounds, Argan oil has traditionally been used as a treatment for skin diseases. It it also has valuable cancer chemopreventive effects and plays a beneficial role in the prevention of cardiovascular problems.\n",
